
### **30-9-2025 Tuesday**

## **Day 4 – Advanced Git & GitHub Collaboration**

1. **Fork a repository from GitHub and clone it locally.**
2. **Set the original repository as an upstream remote.**
3. **Fetch updates from the upstream repository.**
4. **Rebase your branch on top of the upstream main branch.**
5. **Open a pull request on GitHub.**
6. **Use GitHub Issues to track a bug or feature.**
7. **Assign a collaborator to a GitHub Issue.**
8. **Use `git blame` to find who last modified each line in a file.**
9. **Create a `.gitignore` file and add rules to ignore specific files/folders.**
10. **Generate and add an SSH key to your GitHub account for authentication.**

***Solution***

1. git clone https://github.com/username/repo.git
2. git remote add upstream https://github.com/original-owner/original-repo.git
3. git fetch upstream
4. git rebase upstream/main
5. no CLI command  — go to GitHub and open a Pull Request via the website
6. no CLI command — go to GitHub -> Issues -> New Issue
7. no CLI command — on the GitHub issue page, use the "Assignees" sidebar
8. git blame filename.txt
9. touch .gitignore
    echo "node_modules/" >> .gitignore
    echo "*.log" >> .gitignore
    cat .gitignore

10. ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "cat_email@gmail.com"
